params.doc: The downloaded file's name. Defaults to the file's name displayed in the Media Manager

params.name: expirationInMinutes
params.doc: The time (in minutes) it takes for the download URL to expire. Defaults to 600. Limit is 525600 (1 year).

params.name: expirationRedirectUrl
params.doc: The redirect URL for when the download URL with a token has expired. Defaults to a 403 Forbidden response page.

params.name: assetKeys
params.doc:
Optional Asset key
 The asset key is used to download a specific asset of the file
 A special asset key called `src` is used as a default, and describe the original file

docs.summary:
Gets a download URL that includes a temporary token from the Media Manager for a specified file
 Use this to grant access to a private file, or to provide a redirect url after the token expiration

examples.title: Generate a file download url
body:
curl --location --request POST 'www.wixapis.com/site-media/v1/files/2acbb8_7596aeebcf5c41eca01c0d99667ac967.mp3/generate-download-url' \
--header 'Accept: application/json' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
  "downloadFileName": "Gorillaz - Feel Good Inc.mp3",
  "expirationInMinutes": "60",
  "expirationRedirectUrl":"www.mysite.com/store",
  "asset_keys": ["320kbs.mp3"]
}'

Possible values are:
  • FAILED - File upload or processing failed
  • READY - File is ready for consumption
  • PENDING - File is waiting for processing or currently being processed

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • IMAGE
  • VIDEO
  • AUDIO
  • DOCUMENT
  • VECTOR

Possible values are:
  • TUS - Use upload protocol

Possible values are:
  • ASC
  • DESC

  • UNKNOWN
  • HLS
  • DASH
